activeClockDivider.label: active mode clock divider
activeClockDivider.descr: Active mode clock divider, occupy 9 bits, generates CLK_CS clock from CLK_APB clock using F(CS) = F(APB) / (clockDivider+1)

activeDetectPeriod.label: active mode detect period number
activeDetectPeriod.descr: Detect period (how many CLK_CS clock cycles to scan a channel, occupy 16 bits

activeIdlePeriod.label: active mode idle period number
activeIdlePeriod.descr: Idle period (how many clock cycles to wait between channel scans), occupy 16 bits

activeOscFreq.label: active mode oscillator frequency
activeOscFreq.descr: Relaxation oscillator frequency configuration. The value will adjust the current being driven to input channels by equation: 0.4 + 0.2(OSC_FREQ+1) [uA], occupy 6 bits

activeCounterGain.label: active counter gain
activeCounterGain.descr: Can increase counter value by multiplication with this gain, cccupy 8 bits

lowPowerChannelNum.label: low power channel number
lowPowerChannelNum.descr: Indicates how many consecutive CLK_32K cycles need to meet the threshold value before the wake-up interrupt is triggered. The actual interpretation by the hardware of this value is such that one more than the value programmed here is used, occupy 4 bits

lowPowerThreshold.label: low power Threshold
lowPowerThreshold.descr: The value represents the upper bound of the counter output in terms of what is considered a valid touch event, occupy 16 bits

lowPowerDebonceNum.label: low power debonce
lowPowerDebonceNum.descr: Selects which channel index to monitor while in LP mode, occupy 3 bits

lowPowerIdlePeriod.label: low power idle period number
lowPowerIdlePeriod.descr: Idle period between previous scanning end and next scanning start, occupy 16 bits

multiplier.label: signal multiplier
multiplier.descr: Electrode signal multiplier. Enable to adjust the measured raw signal by multiplication operation. It will change the values of all signals except measured raw signal in the electrode scope window. NT name: multiplier

divider.label: signal divider
divider.descr: Electrode signal divider. Enable to adjust the measured raw signal by division operation. It will change the values of all signals except measured raw signal in the electrode scope window. NT name: divider

shield_threshold.label: shield activating threshold
shield_threshold.descr: SH Threshold for shield activating. NT name: shield_threshold

shield_gain.label: shielding gain
shield_gain.descr: SH Gain for shielding el. Signal. NT name: shield_gain

shield_attn.label: shielding attenuate
shield_attn.descr: SH Attenuate for shielding el. Signal. NT name: shield_attn

shield_sens.label: shielding sensitivity limitation
shield_sens.descr: SH Sensitivity for shielding limitation. NT name: shield_sens

pin_input.label: pin input
pin_input.descr: Electrode input pin. NT name: pin_input

gpio_input.label: gpio input
gpio_input.descr: Electrode gpio pin. NT name: gpio_input

baseline_level.label: electrode baseline level
baseline_level.descr: Baseline level to be checked by the safety. If the electrode baseline value exceed below 12.5% or above than 25% of the electrode baseline level the safety fault is detected.

signal_filter.coef1.label: IIR filter coefficient to suppress HF noise
signal_filter.coef1.descr: Scale of the current and previous signals. When the coefficient is higher, the current signal has less strength. The item influences the speed of slow and fast signal waveforms in input signals part of the electrode scope window. NT name: coef1

fast_signal_filter.cutoff.label: fast signal butterworth filter coefficient
fast_signal_filter.cutoff.descr: The coefficient for the implemented butterworth filter polynomial of the fast signal. The item influences the speed of fast signal waveform in input signals part of the electrode scope window. It need to call butterworth filter initialization function to filter coefficient update. NT name: cutoff

slow_signal_filter.cutoff.label: slow signal butterworth filter coefficient
slow_signal_filter.cutoff.descr: The coefficient for the implemented butterworth filter polynomial of the slow signal. The item influences the speed of slow signal waveform in input signals part of the electrode scope window. It need to call butterworth filter initialization function to filter coefficient update. NT name: cutoff

base_avrg.n2_order.label: baseline MA filter rate order
base_avrg.n2_order.descr: The order 2^n moving average filter for baseline signal. The item influences the speed of baseline waveform in input signals part of the electrode scope window. NT name: n2_order

asc.touch_threshold_fall_rate.label: asc-touch threshold fall rate
asc.touch_threshold_fall_rate.descr: Rate of how often the touch threshold can fall. The value represents the time period after each touch threshold will fall down if touch threshold is higher than destination threshold. The item influences the falling down speed of the reset threshold waveform in AFID Dynamic Threshold part of the electrode scope window. NT name: touch_threshold_fall_rate

asc.noise_resets_minimum.label: asc-noise level min. limit
asc.noise_resets_minimum.descr: Noise Resets Minimum. If touch threshold is lower than noise reset minimum (low sensitivity) the touch threshold will be limited to noise level minimum value. The item influences the minimum value of the reset threshold value in AFID Dynamic Threshold part of the electrode scope window and the integration limit in the AFID Integration part of the electrode scope window. NT name: noise_resets_minimum

asc.resets_for_touch.label: asc-touch reset number
asc.resets_for_touch.descr: Number of resets required for touch. The low number causes quicker touch event recognition, high number causes longer integration process. The item influences the delay between real touch and its recognition. NT name: resets_for_touch

reset_rate.label: reset rate
reset_rate.descr: Reset rate of the AFID. Cannot be 0. It can clear integration value to avoid the long-term temperature drift. The item set the integration value to zero in the AFID Integration part of the electrode scope window periodically each reset rate period. NT name: reset_rate

signal_filter.coef1.label: IIR filter coefficient to suppress HF noise
signal_filter.coef1.descr: The input IIR signal filter, used to suppress high-frequency noise on measured signal. When the coefficient is higher, the current signal has less strength. The item influences the speed of measured_iir waveform in signals part of the electrode scope window. NT name: coef1.

base_avrg.n2_order.label: baseline MA filter rate order
base_avrg.n2_order.descr: The moving average filter for the signals in the inactivity state (for example baseline in a touch state). The item influences the speed of measured_iir and predicted waveform in signals part of the electrode scope window in the inactivity state. NT name: n2_order.

non_activity_avrg.n2_order.label: inactivity state MA filter order
non_activity_avrg.n2_order.descr: The moving average filter for the baseline and noise in the release state. The rate should be defined as a modulo of the system period. The item influences the speed of baseline and noise waveform in signals part of the electrode scope window in the release state. NT name: n2_order.

entry_event_cnt.label: touch sample count
entry_event_cnt.descr: Sample count for the touch event. This means that this count of samples must meet the touch condition to trigger a real touch event. The item influences the entry event counter waveform in counter part of the electrode scope window. NT name: entry_event_cnt.

deadband_cnt.label: recover sample count
deadband_cnt.descr: Sample count for the deadband filter. This field specifies the number of samples that cannot proceed to the next event. For Example: after the touch event, a release event with "deadband_cnt" samples can follow. The item influences the deadband counter waveform in counter part of the electrode scope window. NT name: deadband_cnt.

signal_to_noise_ratio.label: signal to noise ratio
signal_to_noise_ratio.descr: Signal-to-noise ratio is used for counting the minimum size of the signal that is ignored. The touch threshold depends on noise and signal-to-noise ratio. This item influences the level of delta signal to make touch event. The item influences the entry event counter waveform in electrode scope window. The item influences the high deadband waveform in raw signal part of the electrode scope window. NT name: signal_to_noise_ratio.

min_noise_limit.label: minimum noise value
min_noise_limit.descr: Minimum noise value influencing the touch threshold value and the intensity of delta signal to make touch event. Used for predicted signal calculation and delta signal filter limits. The item limits the noise waveform in noise part of the electrode scope window. NT name: min_noise_limit.

signal_filter.coef1.label: IIR filter coefficient to suppress HF noise
signal_filter.coef1.descr: The input IIR signal filter, used to suppress high-frequency noise on measured signal. When the coefficient is higher, the current signal has less strength. The item influences the speed of measured_iir waveform in signals part of the electrode scope window. NT name: coef1.

base_avrg.n2_order.label: baseline MA filter rate order
base_avrg.n2_order.descr: The moving average filter for the signals in the inactivity state (for example baseline in a touch state). The item influences the speed of measured_iir and predicted waveform in signals part of the electrode scope window in the inactivity state. NT name: n2_order.

non_activity_avrg.n2_order.label: inactivity state MA filter order
non_activity_avrg.n2_order.descr: The moving average filter for the baseline and noise in the release state. The rate should be defined as a modulo of the system period. The item influences the speed of baseline and noise waveform in signals part of the electrode scope window in the release state. NT name: n2_order.

entry_event_cnt.label: touch sample count
entry_event_cnt.descr: Sample count for the touch event. This means that this count of samples must meet the touch condition to trigger a real touch event. The item influences the entry event counter waveform in counter part of the electrode scope window. NT name: entry_event_cnt.

deadband_cnt.label: recover sample count
deadband_cnt.descr: Sample count for the deadband filter. This field specifies the number of samples that cannot proceed to the next event. For Example: after the touch event, a release event with "deadband_cnt" samples can follow. The item influences the deadband counter waveform in counter part of the electrode scope window. NT name: deadband_cnt.

signal_to_noise_ratio.label: signal to noise ratio
signal_to_noise_ratio.descr: Signal-to-noise ratio is used for counting the minimum size of the signal that is ignored. The touch threshold depends on noise and signal-to-noise ratio. This item influences the level of delta signal to make touch event. The item influences the entry event counter waveform in electrode scope window. The item influences the high dead band waveform in raw signal part of the electrode scope window. NT name: signal_to_noise_ratio.

min_noise_limit.label: minimum noise value
min_noise_limit.descr: Minimum noise value influencing the touch threshold value and the intensity of delta signal to make touch event. Used for predicted signal calculation and delta signal filter limits. The item limits the noise waveform in noise part of the electrode scope window. NT name: min_noise_limit.

dc_track_enabled.label: ignore negative signal drops
dc_track_enabled.descr: Enable or disable DC track feature to avoid negative signal drop below the baseline - used to debounce the short glitches. If enabled and the signal is under baseline longer then defined in dc_track_cnt value the usafa keydetector will be reset. NT name: dc_track_enabled

dc_track_cnt.label: sample number of negative signal
dc_track_cnt.descr: Define minimum number of cycles when signal must fall down below tha baseline to reset the usafa keydetector if DC track functionality is enabled. NT name: dc_track_cnt

time_period.label: system time period [ms]
time_period.descr: Defined time period (triggering period). Can't be 0. NT name: time_period

init_time.label: initialization time [ms]
init_time.descr: Initialization time for the system and calibration. Durring the init time the user can not touch any electrode (incorrect calibration happend if there is the touch event durring initialization). NT name: init_time

safety_period_multiple.label: safety period multiple
safety_period_multiple.descr: safety period multiple specify how offten will be safety test processed (for example selection 10 means that safety tests will be executed 1 time per 10 NXP Touch tasks execution)

safety_crc_hw.label: use HW CRC
safety_crc_hw.descr: use HW CRC instead of SW CRC algoritm (in case the MCU has such CRC peripheral module)

delay_interval.label: safety delay interval [ms]
delay_interval.descr: safety delay interval to be apply between switching pin to gpio and reading value back [ms]

user_interface.label: high counter value for self-cap
user_interface.descr: maximum counter value for self-cap mode. NT name: SelfRangeMax

SelfRangeMin.label: low counter value for self-cap
SelfRangeMin.descr: Minimum counter value for self-cap mode which autocalibrarion try to achieve. NT name: SelfRangeMin

SelfRangeMax.label: high counter value for self-cap
SelfRangeMax.descr: Maximum counter value for self-cap mode which autocalibrarion try to achieve.. NT name: SelfRangeMax

SelfRangeDeltaMin.label: low delta value for self-cap
SelfRangeDeltaMin.descr: Minimum delta value for self-cap mode which autocalibrarion try to achieve.. NT name: SelfRangeDeltaMin

SelfRangeDeltaMax.label: high delta value for self-cap
SelfRangeDeltaMax.descr: Maximum delta value for self-cap mode which autocalibrarion try to achieve.. NT name: SelfRangeDeltaMax

MutRangeMin.label: low counter value for mutual-cap
MutRangeMin.descr: Minimum counter value for mutual-cap mode which autocalibrarion try to achieve.. NT name: MutRangeMin

MutRangeMax.label: high counter value for mutual-cap
MutRangeMax.descr: Maximum counter value for mutual-cap mode which autocalibrarion try to achieve.. NT name: MutRangeMax

MutRangeDeltaMin.label: low delta value for mutual-cap
MutRangeDeltaMin.descr: Minimum delta value for mutual-cap mode which autocalibrarion try to achieve.. NT name: MutRangeDeltaMin

MutRangeDeltaMax.label: high delta value for mutual-cap
MutRangeDeltaMax.descr: Maximum delta value for mutual-cap mode which autocalibrarion try to achieve.. NT name: MutRangeDeltaMax

wtrmark_hi.label: high moodule counter sw threshold
wtrmark_hi.descr: Software high limit. NT name: wtrmark_hi

wtrmark_lo.label: low module counter sw threshold
wtrmark_lo.descr: Software low limit. NT name: wtrmark_lo

range.label: rotary range
range.descr: Maximum range for the position value. NT name: range

range.label: slider range
range.descr: Maximum range for the position value. NT name:

insensitivity.label: insensitivity
insensitivity.descr: Insensitivity for the callbacks invokes when the position is changed. NT name: insensitivity

groups.label: keypad group pointer
groups.descr: Pointer to the group definitions. An array of integers, where bits in the integer represents electrodes in a group. NT name: groups

multi_touch.label: stored keypad multi-touch
multi_touch.descr: Stored keypad multi-touch array. The gesture means the time change of activated keypad electrodes written in hexadecimal format from right to left. For example, gesture 0x321 means that firstly electrode 1 was touched, then electrode 2 and 3. NT name: gesture

range.label: proxi range
range.descr: Max signal delta level for max. proxi (100%) value. NT name: range

scale.label: max counter proxi value
scale.descr: Proxi scale (i.e. 0-100% or 0-255) value. NT name: scale

threshold.label: proxi touch threshold
threshold.descr: Proxi Touch/Release threshold value. NT name: range

insensitivity.label: insensitivity
insensitivity.descr: Insensitivity for the callbacks invokes when the position is changed. NT name:

gesture.label: stored proxi gestrures
gesture.descr: Stored proxi gesture array. The gesture means the time change of activated proxi electrodes written in hexadecimal format from right to left. For example, gesture 0x321 means that firstly electrode 1 was touched, then electrode 2 and 3. NT name: gesture

double_tap_interval.label: double tap interval [ms]
double_tap_interval.descr: Max. time interval between taps for double tap. NT name: double_tap_interval

dissimilarity_max.label: maximum dissimilarity
dissimilarity_max.descr: Maximum difference for unlock gesture recognition. NT name: dissimilarity_max

touchpad_size_horizontal.label: horizontal touchpad size
touchpad_size_horizontal.descr: Number of touchpad segments on x axis (horizontal segments). NT name: touchpad_size_horizontal

touchpad_size_vertical.label: vertical touchpad size
touchpad_size_vertical.descr: Number of touchpad segments on y axis (vertical segments). NT name: touchpad_size_vertical

sensing_mode.label: enable mutual-cap touchpad
sensing_mode.descr: False value means touchpad is based on self-capacitance sensing mode, true value means touchpad is based on mutual-capacitance sensing mode. NT name: sensing_mode

increase_resolution.label: enable increase resolution
increase_resolution.descr: False value means default resolution, true value means that two the nearest touched electrodes create addition position value, it extends resolution according: new_resolution = 2 * default_resolution - 1. NT name: increase_resolution

gesture.label: stored matrix gestures
gesture.descr: Stored matrix gesture array. The gesture means the time change of fingers x and y coordinates written in hexadecimal format from right to left. For example, x coordinate gesture 0x4321 means that firstly x position 1 was touched, then x position 2, 3 and 4. NT name: gesture
